20:34.150 --> 20:37.062
SO, um, I was wondering...

20:38.321 --> 20:39.697
I mean...

20:40.156 --> 20:42.363
Is it really family night on Friday,

20:43.076 --> 20:45.783
or do you think maybe you'd like to go
to that party with me?

20:48.415 --> 20:49.996
Family night was a total lie.

20:52.293 --> 20:53.578
SO is that a yes, you'll go?

20:55.213 --> 20:56.328
Definitely yes.

20:56.589 --> 20:59.296
How can you do this?

20:59.592 --> 21:01.332
We both know that it's wrong

21:01.594 --> 21:06.964
But we keep it going on and on

21:10.353 --> 21:12.969
If it's so clear, then

21:13.231 --> 21:16.064
Why can't you help yourself?

21:17.402 --> 21:19.814
It's people like you that

21:20.071 --> 21:23.780
Always look for someone else to blame

21:58.067 --> 21:59.352
(FAINT RUSTLING)

22:04.032 --> 22:05.317
(GROWL)

22:14.417 --> 22:15.452
(RASPY BREATHING)

22:40.151 --> 22:41.266
(GASPING)

22:52.747 --> 22:54.203
Good morning.

23:01.714 --> 23:03.375
(ZIPPER ZIPS)

23:06.052 --> 23:07.087
All right, little man.

23:08.012 --> 23:09.843
How 'bout you tell me
where you're getting yourjuice.

23:10.306 --> 23:14.515
- What?
- Where are you getting yourjuice?

23:18.314 --> 23:19.690
My mom does all the grocery shopping.

23:21.568 --> 23:22.728
Now, listen, McCall,

23:22.986 --> 23:25.147
you're gonna tell me exactly what it is
and who you're buying it from,

23:25.321 --> 23:28.154
because there's no way in hell you're
out there kicking ass on the field like that

23:28.324 --> 23:29.575
without some sort of chemical boost.

23:30.410 --> 23:32.275
Oh, you mean steroids.

23:33.246 --> 23:34.235
Are you on steroids?

23:34.455 --> 23:36.195
What the hell is going on with you, McCall?

23:36.416 --> 23:39.249
What's going on with me?
You really wanna know?

23:39.544 --> 23:40.704
Well, so would I!

23:40.962 --> 23:42.498
Because I can see, hear, and smell things

23:42.755 --> 23:44.131
that I shouldn't be able
to see, hear, and smell.

23:44.340 --> 23:46.205
I do things that should be impossible,
I'm sleepwalking

23:46.426 --> 23:48.883
three miles into the middle
Of the woods, and I'm pretty much

23:49.137 --> 23:51.048
convinced that I'm totally
out of my freaking mind!

23:52.098 --> 23:53.429
(SIGHS LOUDLY)

23:54.976 --> 23:56.307
(CHUCKLES)

23:56.519 --> 23:59.056
You think you're funny. Don't you, McCall?

24:00.356 --> 24:03.189
I know you're hiding something.
I'm gonna find out what it is.

24:03.610 --> 24:04.725
I don't care how long it takes.

24:04.986 --> 24:06.317
(BANGS LOCKER)

24:09.198 --> 24:11.109
Scott! Scott, wait up.

24:11.367 --> 24:12.982
Stiles, I'm playing the first elimination,
man, can it wait?

24:13.244 --> 24:16.156
Just hold on, Okay?
I overheard my dad on the phone.

24:16.372 --> 24:17.908
The fiber analysis came back
from the lab in LA.

24:18.166 --> 24:19.622
They found animal hairs on the body
from the woods!

24:19.876 --> 24:21.332
- Stiles, I gotta go.
- Wait, no! Scott!

24:21.586 --> 24:23.292
You're not gonna believe
what the animal was!

24:24.589 --> 24:26.204
- It was a wolf.
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)

24:26.382 --> 24:27.713
Let's go! Gather round!

24:27.967 --> 24:30.049
Bring it in, come on!

24:30.303 --> 24:31.338
Come on!

24:34.265 --> 24:35.425
Got a question, McCall?

24:36.559 --> 24:37.514
- What?
- You raised your hand.

24:37.727 --> 24:40.343
- You have a question?
- Oh, no. I was just, uh...

24:41.189 --> 24:42.224
Nothing. Sorry.

24:42.398 --> 24:44.263
Okay. You know how this goes.

24:44.817 --> 24:46.353
If you don't make the cut,

24:47.403 --> 24:49.359
you're most likely sitting on the bench
for the rest of the season.

24:49.572 --> 24:53.360
You make the cut, you play.
Your parents are proud.

24:53.701 --> 24:55.202
Your girlfriend loves ya!

24:55.411 --> 24:56.241
Huh?

24:56.412 --> 24:58.152
Everything else is

24:58.665 --> 24:59.950
cream cheese.

25:00.416 --> 25:03.249
Now, get out there
and show me what you got!

25:03.419 --> 25:05.250
- Come on!
- Let's go! Let's go!

25:05.463 --> 25:06.327
(ALL SHOUTING)

25:06.547 --> 25:08.253
(WHISTLE BLOWS TWICE)

25:08.466 --> 25:10.377
(OVERLAPPING TALKING)

25:11.094 --> 25:12.755
("SHINE" PLAYING)

25:19.644 --> 25:20.884
(GRUNTS)

25:21.396 --> 25:24.433
Because the sun came out to shine

25:25.441 --> 25:28.308
All my dreams came true last night

25:28.528 --> 25:32.271
Because the sun came out to shine

25:32.448 --> 25:34.154
Let it shine

25:34.409 --> 25:36.274
Let it shine

25:36.452 --> 25:41.412
But don't let the sun see you cry

25:42.208 --> 25:43.414
(CHEERING)

25:48.131 --> 25:49.211
Ooh!

25:58.141 --> 25:59.756
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

26:00.018 --> 26:01.383
(LOUD CHEERING)

26:05.606 --> 26:07.107
(ALL WHOOPING)

26:13.322 --> 26:15.278
McCall! Get over here!

26:15.742 --> 26:17.573
What in God's name was that?

26:17.827 --> 26:19.533
This is a lacrosse field.

26:20.038 --> 26:22.245
What, are you trying out
for the gymnastics team?

26:22.457 --> 26:24.243
- NO, Coach.
- What the hell was that?

26:24.459 --> 26:27.246
I don't know.
I was just trying to make the shot.

26:27.462 --> 26:28.998
Yeah, well, you made the shot.

26:29.255 --> 26:30.290
And guess what?

26:31.549 --> 26:32.538
You're startin', buddy.

26:33.634 --> 26:35.716
- You made first line.
- (CROWD CHEERING)

26:35.970 --> 26:37.176
Come on!

26:37.346 --> 26:38.552
BOY: First line!

27:07.835 --> 27:09.371
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

27:15.676 --> 27:18.292
(SIGHS) Get in. You gotta see this thing.

27:19.180 --> 27:21.762
I've been up all night reading.
Websites, books. All this information.

27:22.016 --> 27:23.176
How much Adderall have you had today?

27:23.559 --> 27:25.140
A lot. Doesn't matter. Okay, just listen.

27:25.353 --> 27:27.218
Oh, is this about the body?
Did they find out who did it?

27:27.522 --> 27:29.433
No, they're still questioning people,
even Derek Hale.

27:29.690 --> 27:30.975
Oh, the guy in the woods
that we saw the other day.

27:31.234 --> 27:32.599
Yeah! Yes. But that's not it, okay?

27:33.277 --> 27:35.768
- What, then?
- Remember the joke from the other day?

27:36.489 --> 27:37.729
Not a joke anymore.

27:38.741 --> 27:40.322
The wolf. The bite in the woods.

27:41.077 --> 27:43.614
I started doing all this reading.
DO you even know why a wolf howls?

27:43.871 --> 27:45.702
- Should I?
- It's a signal, Okay?

27:45.957 --> 27:49.040
When a wolf's alone, it howls
to signal its location to the rest of the pack.

27:49.502 --> 27:52.118
SO if you heard a wolf howling, that means
others could have been nearby.

27:52.296 --> 27:54.878
- Maybe even a whole pack Of 'em.
- A whole pack Of wolves?

27:55.299 --> 27:56.914
No, werewolves.

27:59.303 --> 28:01.089
Are you seriously
wasting my time with this?

28:01.305 --> 28:02.920
You know I'm picking up Allison in an hour.

28:03.182 --> 28:04.968
I saw you on the field today, Scott.

28:05.226 --> 28:07.968
Okay, what you did wasn'tjust amazing,
all right? It was impossible.

28:09.147 --> 28:11.183
- Yeah, so I made a good shot.
- No, you made an incredible shot,

28:11.399 --> 28:14.266
I mean, the way you moved, your speed,
your reflexes.

28:14.485 --> 28:16.771
People can't just suddenly
do that overnight.

28:17.196 --> 28:18.527
And there's the vision and the senses,

28:18.781 --> 28:21.158
and don't even think I don't notice
you don't need your inhaler anymore.

28:21.325 --> 28:23.031
Okay! Dude, I can't think about this now.

28:23.327 --> 28:25.067
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- Tomorrow? What? NO!

28:25.329 --> 28:26.409
The full moon's tonight. Don't you get it?

28:26.664 --> 28:28.950
What are you trying to do?
I just made first line.

28:29.208 --> 28:32.075
I got a date with a girl who I can't believe
wants to go out with me,

28:32.336 --> 28:35.078
and everything in my life is somehow
perfect. Why are you trying to ruin it?

28:35.423 --> 28:36.538
I'm trying to help.

28:38.301 --> 28:40.041
You're cursed, Scott.

28:40.761 --> 28:43.173
You know, and it's notjust the moon
will cause you to physically change.

28:43.347 --> 28:46.339
It also just so happens to be
when your bloodlust will be at its peak.

28:47.977 --> 28:50.263
- Bloodlust?
- Yeah, your urge to kill.

28:51.689 --> 28:53.304
I'm already starting to feel
an urge to kill, Stiles.

28:53.774 --> 28:55.230
You gotta hear this.

28:57.486 --> 29:00.569
"The change can be caused by anger
or anything that raises your pulse."

29:01.282 --> 29:03.944
All right? I haven't seen anyone
raise your pulse like Allison does.

29:04.202 --> 29:06.989
You gotta cancel this date.
I'm gonna call her right now.

29:07.246 --> 29:08.326
- What are you doing?
- I'm canceling the date.

29:08.581 --> 29:09.787
No, give it to me!

29:12.335 --> 29:13.791
(GRUNTS)

29:14.045 --> 29:15.251
(PANTING)

29:21.636 --> 29:22.625
I'm sorry.

29:26.307 --> 29:29.049
(STAMMERING)
I gotta go get ready for that party.

29:37.193 --> 29:38.353
I'm sorry.

29:38.861 --> 29:40.692
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

30:03.386 --> 30:04.796
Mom!

30:05.346 --> 30:07.302
Is this a party or a date?

30:09.475 --> 30:10.715
Maybe both.

30:11.310 --> 30:13.471
- And her name is...
- Allison.

30:13.729 --> 30:16.141
Allison. Nice.

30:18.234 --> 30:19.314
Thank you.

30:20.194 --> 30:21.309
We don't need to have a talk, do we?

30:23.072 --> 30:24.528
Mom, I'm not having the safe sex talk
with you.

30:24.782 --> 30:26.488
(LAUGHS) Oh, my God.

30:26.742 --> 30:30.200
NO, I meant about keeping the tank full.
Give me those back.

30:30.413 --> 30:31.448
Are you serious?

30:31.706 --> 30:33.196
You bet your ass I am serious.

30:33.374 --> 30:35.786
I'm not gonna end up
on some reality television show

30:36.043 --> 30:37.328
with a pregnant 16-year-old.

30:37.545 --> 30:39.126
Come on!

30:42.508 --> 30:43.588
(PARKING BRAKE CRAN KS)

30:43.843 --> 30:45.049
(SIGHS)

30:54.437 --> 30:57.349
("THE INTERNET KILLED
THE VIDEO STAR" PLAYING)

31:03.112 --> 31:04.977
The kids are disco dancing

31:05.239 --> 31:07.025
They're tired of rock and roll

31:07.283 --> 31:09.239
I tried to tell 'em, hey

31:09.410 --> 31:10.741
(GROWLING AND BARKING)

31:11.287 --> 31:12.868
But they don't wanna listen

31:20.671 --> 31:24.209
- You Okay?
- What? Yeah. I'm fine.

31:27.678 --> 31:30.841
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh

31:31.098 --> 31:35.262
The Internet killed the video star

31:37.021 --> 31:38.727
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING)

32:14.475 --> 32:16.807
(OVERLAPPING TALKING)

32:18.270 --> 32:19.350
(GRUNTS)

32:21.440 --> 32:22.395
Are you Okay?

32:22.650 --> 32:23.935
(PANTING)

32:26.404 --> 32:27.564
I'll be right back.

32:35.788 --> 32:36.823
YO, Scott, you good?

32:39.583 --> 32:41.198
Are you Okay?

32:48.259 --> 32:49.419
(GRUNTS)

32:50.719 --> 32:52.004
(PANTING)

32:58.894 --> 33:00.054
Allison.

33:01.272 --> 33:02.603
I'm a friend Of Scott's.

33:07.820 --> 33:09.230
My name's Derek.

33:16.912 --> 33:18.197
(PANTING)

33:48.319 --> 33:50.275
(CRACKING AND SQUISHING)

34:03.209 --> 34:04.164
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

34:04.376 --> 34:06.287
- GO away.
- STILES: Scott, it's me.

34:09.340 --> 34:10.955
Let me in, Scott. I can help.

34:11.217 --> 34:13.833
NO! Listen, you gotta find Allison.

34:14.094 --> 34:15.959
She's fine, all right?
I saw her get a ride from the party.

34:16.222 --> 34:18.588
- She's totally fine.
- No, I thinkl know who it is.

34:18.849 --> 34:20.180
You just let me in. We can try...

34:20.392 --> 34:22.769
It's Derek. Derek Hale is the werewolf.
He's the one that bit me.

34:23.020 --> 34:24.931
He's the one that killed
the girl in the woods.

34:27.525 --> 34:30.517
Scott, Derek's the one
who drove Allison from the party.

34:35.866 --> 34:36.946
SCOH!

34:50.297 --> 34:52.253
(GROWLING)

34:53.300 --> 34:55.632
(SQUISHING)

34:58.722 --> 35:00.678
(ROARS)

35:08.315 --> 35:09.270
(THUD)

35:09.525 --> 35:10.890
(GROWLING)

35:15.739 --> 35:17.024
(TIRES SCREECH)

35:26.375 --> 35:27.785
Come on, come on, come on.

35:33.340 --> 35:34.455
(GROWLS)

35:41.640 --> 35:46.009
Hi, Mrs. Argent. You have no idea who I am.
I'm a friend of your daughter's.

35:46.270 --> 35:48.761
Uh, look, this is gonna sound kind of crazy,

35:49.023 --> 35:50.729
really crazy, actually.

35:51.317 --> 35:54.104
- You know what? Crazy doesn't...
- Allison! It's for you.

36:13.339 --> 36:14.920
Where is she?

36:15.758 --> 36:18.295
DEREK: She's safe. From you.

36:20.888 --> 36:21.923
(YELLS)

36:22.181 --> 36:23.512
(BOTH GRUNTING)

36:28.270 --> 36:30.261
- What did you do with her?
- Shh! Quiet.

36:33.192 --> 36:35.524
TOO late. They're already here. Run.

36:44.161 --> 36:46.026
(SCREAMS)

36:46.205 --> 36:47.786
(GROANING)

37:03.222 --> 37:04.177
Take him.

37:06.225 --> 37:07.965
(GRUNTING)

37:10.104 --> 37:11.389
(GRUNTING)

37:15.234 --> 37:16.474
Aah!

37:27.162 --> 37:28.948
(PANTING AND GROANING)

37:37.214 --> 37:40.206
- Who were they?
- Hunters.

37:40.718 --> 37:42.208
The kind that have been
hunting us for centuries.

37:42.845 --> 37:46.178
Us? You mean you! You did this to me!

37:47.558 --> 37:51.096
Is it really so bad, Scott?
That you can see better,

37:51.270 --> 37:54.558
hear more clearly, move faster
than any human could ever hope?

37:56.275 --> 37:58.436
You've been given something
that most people would kill for.

38:00.779 --> 38:02.110
The bite is a gift.

38:02.281 --> 38:03.361
I don't want it.

38:04.742 --> 38:05.697
You will.

38:06.910 --> 38:09.242
And you're gonna need me
if you want to learn how to control it.

38:10.122 --> 38:13.205
SO you and me, Scott, we're brothers now.

38:41.653 --> 38:43.234
You know what actually
worries me the most?

38:43.989 --> 38:46.355
If you say Allison,
I'm gonna punch you in the head.

38:46.617 --> 38:47.823
She probably hates me now.

38:48.076 --> 38:49.111
Ugh.

38:50.162 --> 38:51.151
I doubt that.

38:55.250 --> 38:57.741
Or, you know, you could
just tell her the truth

38:58.003 --> 39:01.587
and revel in the awesomeness
Of the fact that you're a frickin' werewolf.

39:04.468 --> 39:05.457
Okay, bad idea.

39:08.347 --> 39:09.883
Hey, we'll get through this.

39:10.349 --> 39:13.216
Come on, if I have to,
I'll Chain you up myself on full moon nights

39:13.435 --> 39:14.971
and feed you live mice.

39:15.354 --> 39:17.595
I had a boa once. I could do it.

39:18.106 --> 39:19.232
(SCOFFS)

39:26.406 --> 39:28.988
So what happened?
You left me stranded at the party.

39:29.368 --> 39:32.110
Yeah, I know, I know. I'm really sorry, I am.

39:32.746 --> 39:36.204
But you're gonna have to trust
that I had a really good reason.

39:36.375 --> 39:38.206
Did you get sick?

39:38.585 --> 39:40.496
I definitely had an attack of something.

39:42.089 --> 39:43.329
Am I gonna get an explanation?

39:44.341 --> 39:46.127
Can you just find it in your heart
to trust me on this one?

39:48.220 --> 39:49.426
Am I gonna regret this?

39:50.138 --> 39:51.218
Probably.

39:51.557 --> 39:52.888
(LAUGHS)

39:53.475 --> 39:55.215
SO is that a yes on a second chance?

39:55.394 --> 39:56.383
Definitely yes.

39:56.603 --> 39:58.218
(CAR HORN HONKS)

39:58.397 --> 40:00.934
That's my dad. I better go.
